parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS control module can cause the loss of anti-lock braking system (ABS) functionality, leading to extended stopping distances and increased risk of accidents, especially in snowy or wet road conditions.
symptoms: The ABS warning light stays on
the brake warning light flashes
and the vehicle may experience erratic braking performance or a sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intermittent ABS failure can lead to unpredictable braking performance, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in emergency stopping situations.
symptoms: The ABS warning light comes on intermittently
the brake warning light flashes
and the vehicle may experience erratic braking performance or a sudden loss of braking ability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents and potential fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop
or the vehicle fails to stop altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sending unit can cause the fuel gauge to malfunction, leading to inaccurate readings, which can result in running out of fuel, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Fuel gauge reads incorrectly
showing more fuel in the tank than actual
fuel gauge reads empty when tank is full
vehicle stalls due to empty fuel tank
fuel gauge malfunctions in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Supply Fuel Line
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel leak from the supply fuel line can cause a fire hazard, especially when the fuel drips onto the exhaust manifold, which can lead to a vehicle fire.
symptoms: Fuel leak from supply fuel line
intense fuel smell in the cabin
smoke from the exhaust manifold
fuel leak only occurs in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle accelerates on its own
RPM does not drop when accelerator is released
cruise control does not function properly
vehicle accelerates in cold weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The pressure build-up in the gas tank can cause fuel to spray back at the person filling the tank, which can lead to injuries and fires.
symptoms: Pressure builds up in the gas tank when filling
fuel sprays back at the person filling the tank
recall was made for the issue but not for the specific VIN.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical fire in the dashboard can cause a rapid spread of flames, leading to a total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke and flames coming from the dashboard
air vents
or steering wheel
accompanied by a burning plastic or electrical odor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster display can lead to a loss of critical vehicle information, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Faded or illegible display
inability to access vehicle maintenance or safety information
and failure of gauges such as fuel and temperature.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated steering wheel can cause burns to the driver's hands and potentially lead to a fire.
symptoms: Burning or melting of the steering wheel
smoke or flames coming from the steering wheel
and a burning plastic or electrical odor.
